        <div class ='intro'>
             <br>
             This April, Aquidneck Island celebrates Earth Day, all month long! Get outside and explore Aquidneck Island's 69 miles of coastline dotted with over 50 public rights-of-ways. Participate in the challenge to visit the most amount of rights-of-ways to be the All Islander champion!
            
             The goal of this challenge is to visit the most amount of rights-of-ways across the island during the Month of April. The race is on between you and all other students across the island.
             <br>
             <br>
             After visiting a right-of-way, log your trip to get credit and to share some details about your visit. If you make a mistake with your entry, you may edit or delete your entry.
             <br>
             <br>
             This information will be shared with local environmental nonprofits to bring attention to any locations in need of attention and let the public know which spots get the most visits! 
             <br>
             <br>
             At the end of the month, the results will be compiled to see who won the "All Islander Challenge" by visiting the most rights-of-ways.
             <br>
             <br>
             To find your local access points, view them all below! Hint, they are the red dots! 
